The paper deals with the problem of super-resolving light fields, which involves both computer vision (CV) and computer graphics (GR) techniques. The use of deep learning techniques for single image super-resolution (SISR) is a key aspect of the proposed framework, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also involves the use of optical flows, which are commonly used in computer graphics (cs.GR) and computer vision (cs.CV) applications. The paper also involves the use of singular value decomposition (SVD), which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.AI) and linear algebra (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed method using quality metrics, which suggests that it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
